data.title: Pizza 73 Opens 73rd Location in South Calgary
data.meta_description: Pizza 73 welcomes the newest member of its family of restaurants, a new location in South Calgary that earns the distinction of becoming the chain's 73rd store. Located at 5155-130 Avenue SE in Calgary, ...
data.text:
CALGARY, ALBERTA--(Marketwire - Feb 21, 2013) - Pizza 73 welcomes the newest member of its family of restaurants, a new location in South Calgary that earns the distinction of becoming the chain''s 73rd store. Located at 5155-130 Avenue SE in Calgary, the outlet opened on January 26 and will serve both walk-in and delivery customers from 11 a.m. until late, seven days a week.

The 1,195 square foot location offers customers Pizza 73''s complete menu including pizza, chicken wings, chicken bites, wedgies and more. A typical Pizza 73 location employs approximately 10 people on a full and part-time basis.

"The opening of our 73rd store is a milestone that we''ve been looking forward to since the beginning," said Pat Finelli, Chief Marketing Officer for Pizza 73 and Pizza Pizza. "We''re delighted to see the way in which this brand has grown. In 2007, our network comprised of 48 outlets. This important highlight in our company''s history will be etched in our memory and we look forward to new openings in the years ahead."

In celebration of the 73rd store opening, Pizza 73 will be offering 12 pieces of wedgies with savoury ranch dip for $1.73 (regular price $5.75) with the purchase of any Everyday Deal across its entire network of restaurants in Alberta, British Columbia and Saskatchewan.
